  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Enhancing Integrated National Capacity to Respond to COVID-19 in Burundi</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The general objective of this project aims to continue strengthening the capacity of the national authorities to prevent the spread of COVID 19 at targeted points of entry and thereby reduce the devasting effects of the current disease outbreaks on local populations. To achieve this objective, a comprehensive approach through 2 primary components is proposed. IOM will support the national and regional health authorities to set up dignified quarantine/isolation sites for migrants and the host population. In addition, IOM will work with the local authorities to strengthen COVID-19 outbreak surveillance through provision of basic health equipment and materials to five (5) points of entry, as requested by the Government of Burundi. IOM also will support the reinforcement of disease surveillance at borders through provision of trainings for border officials and an increased availability of information on cross-border population movements.</narrative>
  </description>
